<i>Posted by redEye on 03-25-2001 10:59 PM:</i>

<p><b> 9th step and such</b></p>

<p>Excellent walkthrough, Chromite - probably the best I've seen. Well done <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="">.<br />
<br />
As for step 9: The note (Murdrick's Plan) has been given to Captain Berradin, Peffin Ambersnow, and the guy who volunteers to brew the drink; all with no results. Berradin is one of the traitors, I think - how else would he know enough about them to betray them?<br />
<br />
No dwarves other than Murdrick drop anything of interest (heads in particular) when killed. The assuption is that they have to be respawned. The bottleneck is the damned ale.<br />
<br />
The poison is not trivial for a rogue at 250 poison making skill. Annoying, but we can overcome that.<br />
The runed seashell (clouding) is a rare drop off of sirens in Sirens Grotto and only in Sirens Grotto. The ones in Cobalt Scars never seem to drop it. SG is populated by closely packed 51+ mobs, some that are fully MR (i.e. no snare, mez, slow), bad pathing, and very few players (on E'ci, at least). Very hard to get a shell.<br />
<br />
If you manage to get a shell, the brew is a royal bitch. No reported trivial yet (or success, for that matter, though it's not that unlikley that someone's done it and just isn't sharing). Failures have been reported at 195 and 198 brewing skill. Narsty.<br />
<br />
I have to assume that it's a brewing skill check, as it's put in a brew barrel. *shrug*<br />
<br />
Also, one of the components of the ale (ice wyvern stinger) is no drop. Not all that hard to get though. Still no idea on whether the combined ale is no drop or not.<br />
<br />
If anyone has a note and wants to give it to the Grand Historian in ThurgA, I'd be amused to see if he says anything, though I wouldn't expect too much.<br />
<br />
Oh, and the most amusing Rodrick I've seen had 2 daggers (Dirk and velium) and 2 heads (traitor's head and coldain head) <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="">.<br />
<br />
GL to all... it's a VERY fun quest, outside of the competition and farming. Been trying to get ring 8 for weeks now.<br />
<br />
-Redi<br />
Ranger o' Tunare o' 48 seasons, E'ci</p>
