<i>Posted by Tullaian on 03-26-2001 12:33 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Step 9 is a bugger. <br />
<br />
Mind Melt poison is not trivial at Poison 225.. and it can take several hours to collect enough components to attempt several combines at once, if you can find a rogue who has bothered to move their skill up that high. <br />
<br />
The Ale does not appear to be trivial at brewing 200 as nobody has yet posted a succsesful combine despite many brewers with skills in the 190s trying. Anyone who has been practicing brewing knows how hard it is to get skill up that high. Shame I wasted my one shell when i tried at skill in the 120's... sigh. <br />
<br />
The Shell(clouding) is damm rare. 10 hours hunting in SG pulling Sirens did not yield a single shell. <br />
<br />
The hope is that either the final brew is not NO DROP ( but i would be surprised ) or that the step where you hand it to Berradin can be split quested. Otherwise every single person doing this quest will need to become a Grandmaster Brewer.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
