<br />
Anyway, I think the best way to handle this is probably Harmony,.  Try to stop them from attacking and then just pull out the one you want.<br />
<br />
Harmony is a useful tactic for many steps in this quest, but the exact way to use it isn't obvious until after you've already done it once or twice ;-P<br />
