<i>Posted by Indira on 03-27-2001 04:33 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Actually, the best way to handle Scarbrow is to park someone on his spawn point (next to one of the trees down the hill and west of the dorfs, I forget which one exactly unless I'm there looking at it).  The other mobs don't pop right away, and if you aggro him immediately and keep him from running up the hill, none of them will spawn <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="">  Spent an easy evening collecting Frozen Orbs that way.<br />
<br />
I did step 7 with just the help of my cleric to heal me during the fight with Bruke.  I used my longest-range bow and arrow to pull him and got him without the other giants aggroing me, but it'd probably be safer to pull him from behind or to the side (assuming you can hit him through the wall, haven't tried)...the giants spawn outside the front of his building and run towards him; if you can aggro him from behind and back up immediately, you ought to be able to get out of their aggro range before they get to him.  Anyway, killed him, went to Corbin...didn't have to kill the orcs/giants there, someone else was doing it...buffed up and parked my cleric safely out of the way and triggered Corbin.  Followed along, and aggroed everything I could when the mobs attacked him.  I got all the giants and most of the orcs, Corbin managed to survive the other orcs.  Snared all the stuff chasing me, kited some of it past the dorfs to kill it, and ended up with a couple of mobs I let chase me around while Corbin beat them up from behind...Dorf Pet! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""></p>
