<hr>
<i>Posted by Chromite on 06-05-2001 09:56 PM:</i>

<p><b> Re: 8th ring question</b></p>

<p><blockquote><FONT face="arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by aldorian </i><br />
<b>I have a question about the 8th ring quest.  I understand the part about killing the chief, firbrand, oracles, and elites in the courtyard before Garadain shows up.  My question is who kills the line of giants and orcs outside the orc fortress?  Do the Coldain's take care of everything outside the fort?  I'd like to know so I can assemble a big enough army.<br />
<br />
Thanks, <br />
Aldorian </b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Here's how it goes..<br />
<br />
1) You kill all the courtyard spawns.  Chief First always.  Then you kill the 2 giants and the 2 other orcs.<br />
<br />
2) By the time you are done killing those five mobs Garadain will be sending in the dwarven army.  Once those dwarves are engaged on the orcs and giants outside the fort, Garadain will walk in to the orc fort unmolested.<br />
<br />
The only time this will fail at this point is if some jerkweed aggros orcs onto Garadain.  If this happens then Garadain most likely will die and the quest will be ended.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
