<i>Posted by Deorn Trackmaster on 07-25-2001 02:17 PM:</i>

<p><b> Roderick Spawn</b></p>

<p>Last night, I logged in and made my way toward the Orc Fort.  I saw the Orc Messenger on tracking and followed him.<br />
<br />
When I got to the fort, the only person outside was a Necro Fear-kiting elites.  The Orc Messenger made it inside.  Since I had read here that it was rumored that that needed to happen in order for the Orc Emmissary to spawn, I set up camp outside of the CC exit.<br />
<br />
I checked tracking again and I see the Orc Messenger.  I turn and watch him make a trip into the Fort.  I did notice that the Chief was not up at the time.  This happened 2 more times till I didn't see him on tracking anymore.  I did not notice if the cheif was up at this time.<br />
<br />
About 2 mins later, the Orc Emmissary spawned.  I /ooc begging no one to kill him till after Roderick spawned and no one did.  After what seemed like 4-6 mins, Roderick spawned.  I tried to land a snare to pull him, but he resisted it and 4 other attempts.  He also resisted 3 Earthcaller procs.<br />
<br />
A Ranger friend of mine started running from Kael to help when I said that he had spawned.  By the time she arrived, Roderick was dead and I had 26hps left. :lol<br />
<br />
I believe that not only does the Orc Messenger have to make it to the fort, but that the Chief has to be up too.<br />
<br />
I am now the owner of the 6th ring and plan to get the 7th and 8th later this week.  I also dinged 52 on my next solo kill so it was a good night!<br />
<br />
Thanks for all the info from everyone here.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
