<i>Posted by Viken on 08-31-2001 04:10 AM:</i>

<p><b> 9th Ring</b></p>

<p>Hero's Coldain Insignia Ring<br />
AC9 +9STR +9STA +9 SV MAGIC +50hp<br />
Effect: Shield of the Eigth<br />
ALL/ALL<br />
<br />
I did part seven last night with myself (51 RNG) and a 40 monk. The Warden was up so I trained him to the Dwarf camp with the coldain cook. There were four dwarves there. They all fought until the dwarves were dead and the Warden was down to 30%. I agro kited him with flame lick and a level 40 monk whackced him from behind until dead.<br />
<br />
I did the freeing Corbin part solo. I trained the 2 Giant guards to Garadain's camp, then the 3 orcs to Garadain's camp, then handed in my ring and the shackle key, then Corbin respawns with Coldain faction, I harmo him, follow him on his way, then he says "We are almost there" then ~20 seconds later 4 giants and 4 orcs spawn, I immediately kick Corbin and run him back to where we came from, I turn around and see the 4 giants/orcs pathing to wear Corbin would have been, but they don't agro since we are now too far. I run Corbin back to the shore, snare + root, camp, log in, 5 minutes later Corbin starts walking to Dobbin and I get my 7th ring!<br />
<br />
Notes:<br />
<br />
1. The giants DO NOT despawn. They will wander in a large circular path, most likely looking for people like me who are trying to evade the ambush. Make sure they aren't coming toward you/Corbin when you are camping. The path has them walking behind the prison camp towards the shore, then back out again, over and over.<br />
<br />
2. When you log back in Corbin will stand there doing nothing for abouve 5 minutes, while you wonder if you just screwed up the quest. He will also respond to Hails, asking for you to show him the ring and give him the shackle key. Don't be alarmed. Just wait until he starts walking.<br />
<br />
3. Keep yourself camoed while waiting. You don't want to have to deal with ulthors and walruses during this important part of the quest.<br />
<br />
4. Keep Corbin harmonied in case the giants find him. This way you can kick him again and have him follow you instead of agroing on the giants.</p>
